cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or data, please cite the paper."
title: "PEINN: Neutrosophic-Affective Routing for Inference-Time Artificial Moral Agents"
abstract: >-
  PEINN (Principle and Emotion in Neutrosophic Nexus) is a deterministic
  inference-time routing module that fuses a neutrosophic truth-indeterminacy-falsity
  head with an emotion-energy signal and routes each input through one of five modes,
  gating a frozen base model without retraining it or loading a second LLM.
